    <h3>EHDSFunctionalStatus -> ConditionEuCore (with evidence Observations)</h3>
    <a> </a>
    <p></p>
    <p>
  This page explains how conceptual elements from the EHDS logical model are expressed
  in the corresponding FHIR resources used by the Functional Status section of this
  Implementation Guide, using Condition as the primary target and functional assessments
  as evidence with referenced Observations.
    </p>
    <p></p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <strong>Mapping Context</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Source logical model:</strong>
          <a href="https://www.xt-ehr.eu/fhir/models/StructureDefinition-EHDSFunctionalStatus.html" target="_blank">
        EHDSFunctionalStatus
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Target FHIR resources:</strong>
          <a href="https://hl7.eu/fhir/base/2.0.0-ballot/StructureDefinition-condition-eu-core.html">ConditionEuCore</a>,
          <a href="https://hl7.org/fhir/observation.html">Observation</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <p></p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table summary="EHDSFunctionalStatus -> ConditionEuCore (with evidence Observations)">
        <caption>EHDSFunctionalStatus -> ConditionEuCore (with evidence Observations)</caption>
        <thead>
